stylometry: Sensitivity analysis is part of the optimization process. It allows you to choose an input variable such as unit cost, forecasted demand, resources available, etc. and vary that to see what the optimal solution would be for the particular input values. This is important because we can see how our profit or production would and could change as some other variables are varied. This could be helpful if we find we need to produce more we will already have an idea of the optimal production, etc.
